column3: Nice :-) All that by changing one number.\n

Now, I see this warning at the start of bitcoin-qt:

```
libpng warning: iCCP: known incorrect sRGB profile
```

I like the solution though :-) There is some guide to fix at https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Libpng_errors
@paveljanik i think we must take this upstream to the Qt team. It seems to be a Qt issue? Or what do you think?\n

According to notes on the Internet, you can run

```
convert -stripe
```

on the image. The question is, if the profile is not added by your changes...
@paveljanik the issue you reporting is not related to this pull (because this pull did not change and bitmap files). I'll have a look at the sRGB profile issue.\n
Merged too quick... I was going to shed-paint that I liked the green! :p jk\n
